   - Test-Driven Development with Red-Green-Refactor cycle
   - TypeScript with Vitest test framework
   - Integer arithmetic to avoid IEEE 754 floating-point rounding errors
   - `Math.ceil` for surcharges (round in MHPCO's favor = round up charges)
   - `Math.floor` for discounts (round in MHPCO's favor = round down discounts)
   - Building block pricing for components (3 alike = special price)
   - Sequential surcharge application (cursed first, then enchantment on top)
